        <p>We tested 10 tools across the full spectrum over 90 days. Here is the ranking by what each tool actually replaces — by use case, CMS fit, and whether your bottleneck is publishing volume or editorial quality.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-tldr">
          <div class="callout-label">⚡ TL;DR — Pick by your use case</div>
          <p><strong>You're a local business operator:</strong> theStacc ($99/mo Content SEO, $167/mo Bundle). <strong>You're an SEO agency:</strong> Search Atlas (OTTO, $99/mo). <strong>WordPress-first:</strong> Emplibot ($59/mo). <strong>Daily publishing cadence:</strong> RankYak ($49/mo). <strong>Bulk experiments:</strong> Autoblogging.ai ($49/mo).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Don't want to compare 10 tools — just want articles live?</h4>
            <p>theStacc runs research, briefs, writing, SEO optimization, and publishing to WordPress / Webflow / Ghost. <strong>30 SEO articles a month for $99</strong>, or bundle with GBP + social at $167/mo.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">See a live demo <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No card · 15-min walkthrough</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="what-is">What content autopilot actually is</h2>
        <p>Every "content autopilot" tool falls in one of four buckets. Buy by the bucket that matches your goal:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Full-stack autopilot</strong> — theStacc, Search Atlas, Outrank. Research → write → optimize → publish, no human in the loop.</li>
          <li><strong>WordPress-native autopilot</strong> — Emplibot, RankYak. Built around a single CMS for cadence publishing.</li>
          <li><strong>Bulk generators</strong> — Autoblogging.ai, ContentBot, SEO Bot. Cheap output at high volume, less editorial polish.</li>
          <li><strong>Assisted autopilot</strong> — Scalenut Cruise, Arvow. You still hit "approve" on each article before it ships.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ The autopilot trap</div>
          <p>Plenty of tools call themselves "autopilot" but stop at the draft. If you still have to copy-paste into WordPress, add the featured image, and set the schema — <strong>that's not autopilot, that's an AI writer.</strong> Read the pipeline before you buy.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 tools</h2>
        <p>Same keyword list, same niches, same 90-day window.</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Test sites</strong> — 3 fresh domains in SaaS, local services, and ecom.</li>
          <li><strong>Scope</strong> — produce 30 articles per tool over 90 days, same target keywords.</li>
          <li><strong>Measurement</strong> — articles published, time-to-live, on-page SEO score, indexing rate, total cost.</li>
          <li><strong>Total spend</strong> — $2,140 across 10 tools, Mar–May 2026.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What we measured</h3>
        <div class="stat-grid">
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">10</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Tools tested</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">Across all 4 categories</div>
